# Existing Applications Research - Laksh Goyal

> SE SitRep — Sprint 1 research artifact
> Author: Laksh
> Scope: competitor analysis of existing standup / team-coordination / status-tracking tools, broken down by feature, with pros and cons of each, and a final synthesis on where the gap is for our project.

## Why this matters

The prompt explicitly names Steady (formerly Status Hero) as the reference product, and Powell flagged AI agents as the new wrinkle. So before we design anything, we need to know what's already out there, which features are table stakes, which are differentiators, and where the gap is that SE SitRep can fill. Each app below is evaluated on the same axes so we can compare apples to apples.

## Apps reviewed

1. Steady (runsteady.com, formerly Status Hero) — the named competitor
2. Geekbot — the most popular Slack-native standup bot
3. Range — async check-ins with mood and team-culture focus
4. DailyBot — multi-platform standup bot with mood tracking
5. Standuply — agile-ceremony automation (standups, retros, planning poker)
6. Jell — OKR/performance-focused check-ins
7. Slack Workflow Builder — native, free baseline
8. Linear / Jira (briefly) — adjacent, for blocker and ticket context

