## 4. DailyBot

Slack/Teams/Google Chat/Discord standup bot, the "jack of all trades" of the category.

### Features

- Async standups with AI-powered blocker detection and risk flagging from check-in text
- Mood tracking, plus pro health-check templates
- Kudos, rewards, and gamification for team-building
- Custom slash commands and no-code automation builder
- Multi-language support (English, Spanish, Portuguese)
- Free starter plan; Essentials at $2.10/user/month, Advanced at $3.60/user/month for AI features
- Multi-team setup with sub-teams and roles
- Exports to PDF, CSV, XLS

### Pros

- Widest platform support; only tool that covers all 4 chat platforms
- AI blocker detection from natural language is closer to what the SE SitRep prompt actually asks for than any other tool
- Gamification + kudos cover the team-building angle without needing Range
- Multi-team and sub-team support out of the box, unlike Geekbot
- Cheaper than Geekbot per seat

### Cons

- Tries to do a lot, so the interface feels overbuilt if you only want standups (Vereda AI review)
- Free tier capped at 3 users
- AI features gated behind the more expensive plan
- Still question-based at its core, so still suffers from low-effort answers
- No AI agent tracking

